(%), as well as computational complexity measured in FLOPs (floating-point operations) for a single clip input of spatial size 
224 2 . #F indicates the number of frames sampled from each video clip. We follow the common setting to sample multiple clips 
per video (10 for Kinetics-400, 2 for Something-Something V1).
